Therefore, I recommend the test from the age of 50 years or 40 years, if you have a direct relative who has already been diagnosed with prostate cancer.
Men of African-American origin are also at higher risk.
The most important thing is to make the right decision once a cancer has been detected.
There are cancers that are aggressive and others that are indolent.
