While the judge of the case points out that creditors must be subject to the bankruptcy law of the United States, the court of appeal of the Fifth Circuit, based in New Orleans, first says that the main proceedings are the trade dispute dealt with in Mexico.
The first point would mean that international cooperation in insolvency procedures for companies with a cross-border profile is not known.
